
[1]foulmouthed

   FOUL'MOUTHED, a. Using language scurrilous, opprobrious, obscene or
   profane; uttering abuse, or profane or obscene words; accustomed to use
   bad language.

   So foulmouthed a witness never appeared in any cause.
